      "span_text": "Most of the knowledge on metal complexes in xylem and phloem has been gained using plants (mostly hyperaccumulators) grown on hydroponics with either a short-time excess metal supply treatment or with a established metal deficiency followed by a short-time metal re-supply treatment (the latter in the case of Fe or Zn). Since these conditions are far from the natural ones, some of the reported metal species can differ from the actual complexes existing in plants in natural conditions [CITATION_1] ."
